arXiv:2510.26331v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We investigate the following Robin eigenvalue problem  egin{equation*} \left\{  egin{array}{ll} -\Delta u=\mu u\,\, &	ext{in}\,\, B,\ \partial_	exttt{n} u+\alpha u=0 &	ext{on}\,\, \partial B \end{array} ight. \end{equation*} on the unit ball of $\mathbb{R}^N$. We obtain the complete spectral structure of this problem. In particular, for $\alpha>0$, we find that the first eigenvalue is $k_{
u,1}^2$ and the second eigenvalue is exactly $k_{
u+1,1}^2$, where $k_{
u+l,m}$ is the $m$th positive zero of $kJ_{
u+l+1}(k)-(\alpha+l) J_{
u+l}(k)$. Moreover, when $\alpha\in(-1,0)$, the first eigenvalue is $-\widehat{k}_{
u,1}^2$ where $\widehat{k}_{
u,1}$ denotes the unique zero of $\alpha I_{
u}(k)+kI_{
u+1}(k)$, and the second eigenvalue is exactly $k_{
u+1,1}^2$. Furthermore, for $\alpha=-1$, the first eigenvalue is $-\widehat{k}_{
u,1}^2$ and the second eigenvalue is exactly $0$. Our conclusions indicate the ratio $\mu_2/\mu_1$ may be positive, negative or zero according to the suitable ranges of the parameter $\alpha$.
